OL,3,CNorth West MP urges curbs on noisy
OL,4,Cfireworks
OL,6,FShe says it is not about banning
OL,7,Ffireworks or organised displays which
OL,8,Fare an important part of celebrations,
OL,9,Fbut instead "the impact of loud,
OL,10,Funpredictable fireworks going off late
OL,11,Fat night... sudden explosions in
OL,12,Fresidential streets at eleven o'clock,
OL,13,Fmidnight, or even later. These bangs
OL,14,Fstartle children, frighten older
OL,15,Fpeople, distress pets and livestock,
OL,16,Fand overwhelm people managing health
OL,17,Fconditions or trauma".
OL,19,FSpeaking in the Commons earlier she
OL,20,Fsaid polls show 85% of people want
OL,21,Fstronger rules on fireworks.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
